      "message": "You are right. I missed the fact, that in GerritInstanceIdProvider `gerrit.instanceId` must not be set:\n\n  @Inject\n  public GerritInstanceIdProvider(@GerritServerConfig Config cfg) {\n    instanceId \u003d cfg.getString(\"gerrit\", null, \"instanceId\");\n  }\n\nSo now, your new test annotation makes much more sense to me. The annotation simulates, that gerrit.instanceId was set.\n\nBut then, it seems that you are missing some use cases:\n\n* GerritInstanceId is null\n* event instanceId set to some value. This can happens if two servers were misconfigured. In one server gerrit.instanceId was set to `foo`so that all events from this server would have instanceId assigned. In another server gerrit.instanceId  wasn\u0027t set. \n\nSo that the check if there is a mismatch and the event should be dropped should extended to something like:\nSomething like:\n\n  public boolean eventSourceMismatch(RefEvent event) {\n    if (instanceId \u003d\u003d null \u0026\u0026 event.instanceId \u003d\u003d null) return true;\n    if (instanceId !\u003d null \u0026\u0026 event.instanceId \u003d\u003d null) return false;\n    if (instanceId \u003d\u003d null \u0026\u0026 event.instanceId !\u003d null) return false;\n    return instanceId.equals(event.instanceId);\n  }\n\nAlso you would need additional test, without your new annotation and still assert that the event was dropped, something like:\n\n  // Not annotation means, we haven\u0027t configured any instanceId\n  public void testIsNotEnabledEventFromForeignInstanceId() {\n    String[] branches \u003d {};\n    setupIsEnabled(\"true\", null, null, branches);\n\n    PatchSetCreatedEvent event \u003d new PatchSetCreatedEvent(testChange(\"testProject\", \"testBranch\"));\n    // Simulate, that another server, the event is coming from, has configured instanceId,\n    //  so that we have a mismatch \n    event.instanceId \u003d \"foreign-instance-id\";\n\n    ItsConfig itsConfig \u003d createItsConfig();\n\n    assertFalse(itsConfig.isEnabled(event));\n    assertLogMessageContains(\"is coming from a remote Gerrit instance-id\");\n  }",
